# Asia Mix CRM - Working Memory

- Treat this repo as web-first (Vercel + Supabase). Do not prioritize APK/mobile work unless the user explicitly asks.
- Authentication uses `public.users` login/password lookup (not Supabase Auth). Do not silently migrate auth flow during unrelated tasks.
- For database setup on a fresh Supabase project: run `supabase/schema.sql` first, then `supabase/migrations/*`, then optional seeds.
- `seed-users.sql` is intentional test data (fixed UUIDs, `admin` password). Do not "fix" it unless user requests.
- Avoid running root-level manual SQL patches in `supabase/migration_*.sql` unless a specific missing feature requires it.
- Keep Vercel and Supabase project alignment explicit: `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`, `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`.
- Before broad refactors, confirm scope with user; prefer minimal targeted fixes.
- For mobile header/layout issues, test narrow breakpoints first (`<640px`) before touching desktop styles.
- Never commit local machine artifacts: `.env*` (except examples), `supabase/.temp/`, Android local SDK paths.
- When resuming after a pause, read `docs/WORKING_MEMORY.md` first, then inspect only files related to the current request.
